Major 7: 1−3−5−7

Dominant 7: 1−3−5−♭7

Minor 7: 1−♭3−5−♭7

Half-Diminished (m7♭5): 1−♭3−♭5−♭7

Diminished 7: 1−♭3−♭5−♭♭7



Start by playing the Root in the LH and the 3rd and 7th (the "guide tones") in the RH. This is the skeleton of the jazz sound.


Practice ii−V−I in all 12 keys.

    Example in C: Dm7→G7→Cmaj7.